Gordon for once is exactly right on this one.  When there have been bugs where items dropped off the wrong mobs, people didn't have to turn those items in.  The items are NOT being changed, they are replaced by other items.  There's nothing to say that the mobs won't get item updates over the course of time.<P>This applies to EVERYTHING in the game.  Verant has the right at any time to change the items that specific mobs will have on them.  This could mean that guards get armor/weapon upgrades, Dvinn could get something better, the levels of mobs could be increased, etc.  If players can improve their abilities and equiptment, so can the NPCs and mobs.  We should all be thankful that we don't see orcs running around with better equiptment from that adventurer they managed to kill.  Do you realize how much harder it would be if the mobs could loot an item off the players they kill? Oh, I'm sorry, we didn't tell you that Drolvargs could now end up with the awesome armor from the adventurers they killed.  Of course, that would increase the challenge in every zone, where if you come across a corpse that hasn't been looted, it may be a good idea to pull that corpse to a "safe" spot to keep the mobs from looting it.<P>
