They arn't makeing a change to any items, they did the change to the drop tables.  BIG BIG difference.  They arn't going to upgrade the lame items that dropped, they are going to make it so the items that are dropped are better.  Different items.  <P>An example of where Verant SHOULD make a change:  Karnor's Castle<BR>Many mobs have a rare drop of a backpack.  Yes, a common, 8 slot, non magical, backpack that is available for sale all over Norrath.  Now, the backpack that drops is normal, same exact item that you can buy in a cleric guild.  If Verant decides to upgrade the item, are they going to upgrade everyone who has a backpack?  Of course not, they will change the drop table, so the backpack that drops is a weight reducer, or a 10 slot, or something along those lines.<P>VP loot is exactly the same.  The mobs dropped a lot of garbage.  You could get the same garbage all over, so they changed the drops to be different items.  They arn't changing any items here.  The issue of an item nerf is when you take items that are in a player's inventory, and change the stats/benefits of the item to something worse than it was before.  When this happens, it's reasonable that people complain.  When a mob starts dropping better loot, your best choice is to kill the mob again.  Complaining because you got there too early for the good stuff is like saying you bought something, then 6 months later, the price dropped.  You don't go back to the store if it's been 6 months(you might if it was within 30 days).<BR>
